Definition: a method of behavior therapy based on the inhibition of one response by the occurrence of another response that is mutually incompatible with it
Example: a relaxation response might be conditioned to a stimulus that previously evoked anxiety
Synonyms: reciprocal-inhibition_therapy, behavior_therapy, a, method, of, behavior, therapy, based, on, the, inhibition, one, response, by, occurrence, another, that, is, mutually, incompatible, with, it, relaxation, might, be, conditioned, to, stimulus, previously, evoked, anxiety
Category: noun.act
